#compdef golem-cli
# =============================================================================
# golem-cli — Golem Cloud's "Command line interface for Golem" —
#             the Rust CLI for Golem Cloud's "agent-native
#             platform for building AI agents and distributed
#             applications that never lose state, never duplicate
#             work, and never require you to build infrastructure".
#             Golem is a WebAssembly-based durable execution
#             platform; golem-cli is the local development +
#             deployment + administration tool for it.
#             Distinguishing from kubectl/docker/cargo/etc. by:
#               - DURABLE EXECUTION model — every "agent" (a
#                 typed WASM component instance) preserves its
#                 entire state + execution stack across crashes,
#                 restarts, and updates
#               - APPLICATION-MANIFEST-DRIVEN: golem.yaml at the
#                 repo root declares components, agents, and
#                 deployment topology
#               - 16 SUBCOMMAND GROUPS: new/templates/build/repl/
#                 deploy/clean/update-agents/redeploy-agents/exec/
#                 + nested account/api/api-token/component/
#                 environment/plugin/profile/resource-definition/
#                 retry-policy/server/agent/agent-type
#               - BRIDGE SDK GENERATION via WASM Interface Types
#                 (wit) → typed language-specific clients
#                 (`generate-bridge` subcommand)
#               - TYPESCRIPT REPL for interactive agent invocation
#                 with auto-imported Bridge SDK clients
#               - GLOBAL --format FLAG: text/json/yaml output
#                 selectable via -F/--format
#               - LOCAL VS. CLOUD ENVIRONMENT TOGGLES: -L/--local
#                 vs -C/--cloud short flags
#               - PLAN MODE: --plan for non-destructive deploy
#                 preview with human-readable diff
#               - comfy-table TABLE RENDERING: every list/show
#                 output (component list, deployment list, plan
#                 diff summary) rendered through comfy-table's
#                 builder-with-render Style API
#             Used by: developers building durable AI agents +
#             stateful distributed applications on Golem Cloud's
#             WASM runtime, and as a reference implementation of
#             a large clap-derive + comfy-table CLI.
#
# Author:  Golem Cloud (golemcloud organization on GitHub) — early-
#          stage company building agent-native durable-execution
#          platform on WebAssembly + Component Model.  Continuous
#          development through 2026 with extensive Rust workspace
#          (cli/, golem-client/, golem-common/, golem-wasm/, etc.).
# Source:  https://github.com/golemcloud/golem
#          https://github.com/golemcloud/golem/blob/main/cli/golem-cli/Cargo.toml
#          https://github.com/golemcloud/golem/blob/main/cli/golem-cli/src/command.rs
# CLI:     cli/golem-cli/src/command.rs — clap derive (`#[derive(
#          Subcommand)]`) with 22+ subcommands, GolemCliGlobalFlags
#          struct with 10+ globally-flattened flags
#          (--format/-F, --environment/-E, --local/-L, --cloud/-C,
#          --app-manifest-path/-A, --disable-app-manifest-
#          discovery/-X, --preset/-P, --profile, --config-dir,
#          --yes/-Y, --show-sensitive).  Headline library:
#          **comfy-table** (clap-derive is well-documented across
#          many Rust completions — comfy-table is the new variant
#          being documented here).
# Library: comfy-table (https://github.com/Nukesor/comfy-table)
#          ("comfy-table" — Arne Beer (Nukesor) — released 2020
#           as a "stylish modern Rust library to format dynamic
#           tabular data".  Distinct from tabled (zhiburt/tabled
#           R609), prettytable-rs, cli-table (Rust), and term-
#           table by being:
#             1. BUILDER-WITH-RENDER API — table.add_row(...) +
#                table.to_string() with no derive macro; pure
#                imperative builder pattern
#             2. CONTENT-ARRANGEMENT ENUM — table.set_content_
#                arrangement(ContentArrangement::Dynamic) controls
#                column-width strategy (Disabled / Static /
#                Dynamic / DynamicFullWidth)
#             3. 12 PRE-DEFINED PRESETS — UTF8_FULL, UTF8_BORDERS_
#                ONLY, UTF8_HORIZONTAL_ONLY, UTF8_NO_BORDERS,
#                NOTHING, ASCII_FULL, ASCII_FULL_CONDENSED,
#                ASCII_BORDERS_ONLY, ASCII_BORDERS_ONLY_CONDENSED,
#                ASCII_HORIZONTAL_ONLY, ASCII_MARKDOWN, plus
#                custom-character override via table.load_preset(
#                "<17-char string>")
#             4. MODIFIERS — table.apply_modifier(UTF8_ROUND_
#                CORNERS) + .apply_modifier(UTF8_SOLID_INNER_
#                BORDERS) compose on top of presets
#             5. PER-CELL/COLUMN STYLE — Cell::new(value).set_
#                alignment(CellAlignment::Right).fg(Color::Green)
#                .bg(Color::DarkRed).add_attribute(Attribute::Bold)
#             6. TERMINAL-WIDTH-AWARE — auto-detects terminal
#                width via crossterm and uses
#                ContentArrangement::Dynamic to fit columns
#             7. TRUECOLOR + 256-COLOR + 16-COLOR support via
#                crossterm's Color enum with full backwards-
#                compatibility down to 16-color terminals)
# License: Apache-2.0 OR Golem Source License v1.1 (golem-cli);
#          MIT (comfy-table)
# Status:  golem-cli — 1,600+ stars on golemcloud/golem (workspace);
#          comfy-table — 1,100+ stars on Nukesor/comfy-table, ~40M
#          crates.io downloads, foundational dependency of golem-
#          cli + pimalaya/himalaya (6.3k stars) + prefix-dev/pixi
#          (7.2k stars) + databricks/click (1.5k stars) +
#          nextstrain/nextclade + lakehq/sail + cmccomb/rust-automl
#          + golemcloud/golem (THIS) + comit-network/xmr-btc-swap
#          + 500+ Rust CLIs needing dynamic-width terminal tables.
