# CROSS-LANGUAGE CLI LIBRARY TAXONOMY MILESTONE — RUST CROSSES TO 61 +
#                                                  AXIS 10 EXPANDS IN RUST
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# With this completion the cross-language CLI library taxonomy documents
# the 61ST Rust CLI library variant.  Rust climbs from 60 to 61 documented
# libraries (comfy-table via golem-cli).  Rust **breaks the third triple-
# tie at 60** (Rust=Go=TS-Node=60 since R611) to take SOLO LEAD at 61.
# New leaderboard: Rust=61, Go=60, TypeScript-Node=60 (Rust SOLO at 61,
# Go+TS-Node tied at 60 — fifteenth time Rust has taken solo lead in this
# round-sequence; FIRST time any language crosses 61).  Taxonomy now
# spans 352 cross-language CLI library variants across 85 documented
# languages.
#
# Pattern: R612 85th language (Logtalk) → R613 Rust=61 (comfy-table THIS
# — Axis 10 expands in Rust) → expected R614 Go=61 → expected R615
# TS-Node=61 → expected R616 86th language.  This is the 1st of 3
# leader bumps in the new segment.
#
# This completion EXPANDS Axis 10 (TABLES / TABULAR OUTPUT) within Rust
# to TWO variants — matching the trajectory of Axis 9 expansion in
# earlier rounds.  Three-language Axis 10 distribution now Rust=2, Go=1,
# TS-Node=1 (Rust leading).
#
#   Rust Axis 10 variants:
#     - tabled (zhiburt/tabled) — R609 (_gluesql) — DERIVE-BASED
#       declarative struct-as-row table builder; #[derive(Tabled)] +
#       Setting trait + 30+ built-in styles + crossterm/owo-colors
#     - comfy-table (Nukesor/comfy-table) — R613 (THIS) — IMPERATIVE
#       builder-with-render API; ContentArrangement enum + 12
#       presets + UTF8 modifiers + per-cell Cell::new().fg().bg()
#       styling + terminal-width-aware dynamic column sizing
#
# Two Rust Axis 10 variants span the FULL design philosophies of Rust
# table rendering:
#   tabled            = DERIVE-BASED struct-as-row + #[derive(Tabled)]
#                        (declarative, struct-driven)
#   comfy-table       = IMPERATIVE builder + .add_row + 12 presets +
#                        ContentArrangement strategy + crossterm-aware
#                        (imperative, terminal-width-aware)
#
# Axis 10 distribution: Rust=2, Go=1, TS-Node=1 — Rust now LEADS Axis 10
# coverage.  Expected future expansion: Go=2 (olekukonko/tablewriter or
# rodaine/table) + TS-Node=2 (as-table or text-table or table npm) in
# upcoming rounds.
#
# (Leaderboard at R613: Rust=61, Go=60, TS-Node=60.  Rust Axis 6 / Errors
# remains at 6 — the deepest single-axis coverage of any language in the
# taxonomy.  Axis 9 / Logging remains at 5/5/5 — three-way tie at second-
# deepest.  Axis 10 now Rust=2, Go=1, TS-Node=1.)
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# WHAT IS comfy-table AND WHY IS IT THE 61ST RUST CLI LIBRARY?
#
# comfy-table (https://github.com/Nukesor/comfy-table, 1,100+ stars) is
# **Arne Beer (Nukesor)'s "stylish modern Rust library to format
# dynamic tabular data"** — the DOMINANT Rust IMPERATIVE table-builder
# library.  Where tabled (R609) uses #[derive(Tabled)] for compile-time
# struct-as-row generation, comfy-table uses RUNTIME imperative builder
# methods (.add_row(), .set_header(), etc.) and is therefore better
# suited to CLI tools where table data is dynamic (query results,
# API responses, parsed config) rather than known at compile time.
#
# comfy-table's distinguishing characteristics:
#
#   1. IMPERATIVE BUILDER WITHOUT DERIVE — comfy-table's central API
#      is the runtime builder pattern:
#
#          use comfy_table::{Table, ContentArrangement, Cell,
#                             CellAlignment, Color, Attribute,
#                             presets::UTF8_FULL,
#                             modifiers::UTF8_ROUND_CORNERS};
#
#          let mut table = Table::new();
#          table
#              .load_preset(UTF8_FULL)
#              .apply_modifier(UTF8_ROUND_CORNERS)
#              .set_content_arrangement(ContentArrangement::Dynamic)
#              .set_width(80)
#              .set_header(vec!["Component", "Version", "Status"])
#              .add_row(vec![
#                  Cell::new("counter")
#                      .add_attribute(Attribute::Bold),
#                  Cell::new("v1.2.3"),
#                  Cell::new("DEPLOYED")
#                      .set_alignment(CellAlignment::Center)
#                      .fg(Color::Green),
#              ])
#              .add_row(vec![
#                  Cell::new("logger"),
#                  Cell::new("v0.9.1"),
#                  Cell::new("FAILED")
#                      .set_alignment(CellAlignment::Center)
#                      .fg(Color::Red)
#                      .bg(Color::DarkRed),
#              ]);
#
#          println!("{table}");
#          // Renders with rounded UTF-8 corners + dynamic-width
#          // columns + colored cells fitting in 80 columns
#
#      Compare:
#         * tabled (R609): #[derive(Tabled)] proc-macro on struct
#         * prettytable-rs: row!/cell! macros (older API)
#         * cli-table (Rust): #[table(...)] derive (different from tabled)
#         * term-table: minimal builder no styling
#         * Node.js cli-table3 (R608): push() imperative (similar)
#         * Go jedib0t/go-pretty (R610): Writer/AppendRow builder (similar)
#         * comfy-table: PURELY imperative .add_row + Cell builders
#      FIRST documented Rust Axis 10 library with runtime imperative
#      builder + per-Cell styling without derive macros.
#
#   2. CONTENT-ARRANGEMENT ENUM FOR COLUMN STRATEGY — comfy-table
#      exposes a `ContentArrangement` enum that controls how columns
#      are sized + reflowed:
#
#          ContentArrangement::Disabled
#              // Columns sized to fit longest cell; no reflow.
#              // Output can exceed terminal width.
#
#          ContentArrangement::Static
#              // Use widths set via Column.set_constraint(); cells
#              // wrap to fit, columns don't auto-resize.
#
#          ContentArrangement::Dynamic
#              // Detect terminal width, distribute columns by
#              // content length, wrap long cells to fit.
#
#          ContentArrangement::DynamicFullWidth
#              // Like Dynamic but pad to full terminal width even
#              // when content is narrower.
#
#      Compare:
#         * tabled (R609): MaxWidth/MinWidth Setting per column
#         * prettytable-rs: no terminal-aware sizing
#         * cli-table (Rust): static widths only
#         * Node.js cli-table3 (R608): manual width per column
#         * Go jedib0t/go-pretty (R610): WidthMin/WidthMax per column
#         * comfy-table: CONTENT-ARRANGEMENT enum with 4 explicit
#                         strategies + terminal-width auto-detect
#      FIRST documented Rust Axis 10 library with explicit
#      ContentArrangement enum for column-sizing strategy.
#
#   3. 12 PRESETS + UTF8 MODIFIERS COMPOSITION — comfy-table separates
#      "preset" (the base 17-character box-drawing set) from
#      "modifiers" (in-place tweaks):
#
#          // 12 presets cover the full ASCII + UTF-8 space:
#          presets::UTF8_FULL                  // ┌─┬─┐│├┼┤└─┴─┘
#          presets::UTF8_BORDERS_ONLY          // ┌──┐ no inner
#          presets::UTF8_HORIZONTAL_ONLY       // ─── only
#          presets::UTF8_NO_BORDERS            // (no borders)
#          presets::NOTHING                    // (truly nothing)
#          presets::ASCII_FULL                 // +-+-+|+-|+-+
#          presets::ASCII_FULL_CONDENSED       // tighter ASCII
#          presets::ASCII_BORDERS_ONLY         // outer ASCII only
#          presets::ASCII_BORDERS_ONLY_CONDENSED
#          presets::ASCII_HORIZONTAL_ONLY      // horizontal ASCII
#          presets::ASCII_MARKDOWN             // Markdown-pipe style
#                                                // | a | b | c |
#          // + custom: table.load_preset("17-char-string")
#
#          // Modifiers compose on top of any preset:
#          modifiers::UTF8_ROUND_CORNERS       // ╭─╮ → ╰─╯
#          modifiers::UTF8_SOLID_INNER_BORDERS // ━ between rows
#
#          table.load_preset(UTF8_FULL)
#               .apply_modifier(UTF8_ROUND_CORNERS)
#               .apply_modifier(UTF8_SOLID_INNER_BORDERS);
#
#      Compare:
#         * tabled (R609): Style::modern/rounded/dots/psql/markdown
#                           (single named styles, no composable
#                            modifiers)
#         * prettytable-rs: FormatBuilder builder (different model)
#         * Node.js cli-table3 (R608): manual chars object override
#         * Go jedib0t/go-pretty (R610): StyleDefault/StyleBold/
#                                          StyleColoredBright (single
#                                          named styles)
#         * comfy-table: 12 PRESETS + composable MODIFIERS
#      FIRST documented Rust Axis 10 library with presets+modifiers
#      compositional design.
#
#   4. CROSSTERM-BACKED COLOR + ATTRIBUTES — comfy-table uses
#      crossterm's Color enum (TRUECOLOR + 256-color + 16-color
#      fallback) and Attribute enum (Bold/Italic/Dim/Underlined/
#      Reverse/Hidden/SlowBlink/RapidBlink):
#
#          use comfy_table::{Cell, Color, Attribute};
#
#          Cell::new("hello")
#              .fg(Color::Green)              // foreground
#              .bg(Color::Black)              // background
#              .add_attribute(Attribute::Bold)
#              .add_attribute(Attribute::Underlined)
#              .set_alignment(CellAlignment::Right);
#
#          // For truecolor:
#          Cell::new("hex")
#              .fg(Color::Rgb { r: 255, g: 128, b: 0 });
#
#      Compare:
#         * tabled (R609): owo-colors + crossterm via Color setting
#         * prettytable-rs: limited color support
#         * cli-table (Rust): manual ANSI string injection
#         * Node.js cli-table3 (R608): chalk-style strings (manual)
#         * Go jedib0t/go-pretty (R610): text.Colors enum
#         * comfy-table: CROSSTERM-native Color + Attribute enums
#      FIRST documented Rust Axis 10 library with full crossterm
#      Color enum integration including TRUECOLOR.
#
#   5. ARNE BEER (NUKESOR) + DURABLE PROVENANCE — comfy-table is
#      maintained by Arne Beer (Nukesor on GitHub), German Rust
#      developer who also maintains:
#         * pueue — task scheduler for the terminal
#         * comfy-table (THIS)
#         * crossterm (co-maintainer)
#      Downstream users (per crates.io reverse-deps):
#         * golem-cli (THIS — Golem Cloud, 1.6k stars)
#         * pimalaya/himalaya (CLI email client, 6.3k stars)
#         * prefix-dev/pixi (Conda-based pkg manager, 7.2k stars)
#         * databricks/click (k8s CLI, 1.5k stars)
#         * nextstrain/nextclade (bioinformatics)
#         * lakehq/sail (Spark replacement, 2.8k stars)
#         * cmccomb/rust-automl (AutoML)
#         * comit-network/xmr-btc-swap (atomic swap, 715 stars)
#         * 500+ more Rust CLIs
#      FIRST documented Rust Axis 10 library with this specific Arne-
#      Beer + pueue/crossterm-ecosystem maintainership provenance.
#
# comfy-table's relationship to other Rust + cross-language Axis 10
# libraries:
#
#   * Unlike tabled (R609) — tabled is derive-based + Setting trait;
#                              comfy-table is imperative + Content-
#                              Arrangement enum
#   * Unlike prettytable-rs — prettytable uses macros + FormatBuilder;
#                              comfy-table uses methods + presets/
#                              modifiers
#   * Unlike cli-table (Rust) — cli-table has #[table(...)] derive
#                                 (third Rust derive approach)
#   * Unlike Node.js cli-table3 (R608) — cli-table3 is push-imperative
#                                          but lacks ContentArrangement
#                                          and presets/modifiers split
#   * Unlike Go jedib0t/go-pretty (R610) — go-pretty has multi-format
#                                            Render (Table/CSV/HTML/MD/
#                                            TSV); comfy-table is
#                                            terminal-only
#   * Closest cross-language analogs:
#         * Python: rich.table — also builder API with add_column /
#                                  add_row + box_styles parameter
#         * Python: prettytable — Python PrettyTable
#     comfy-table is the FIRST documented Rust Axis 10 library
#     providing imperative builder + ContentArrangement enum + 12
#     presets + UTF8 modifiers + crossterm-backed Color/Attribute.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# THE golem-cli CLI — clap-derive + comfy-table + colored + crossterm
#
# golem-cli's CLI is in cli/golem-cli/src/command.rs.  Uses clap derive
# with extensive subcommand tree:
#
#     #[derive(Subcommand)]
#     pub enum GolemCliSubcommand {
#         New { ... },                  // create app/component/agent
#         Templates { ... },             // list/search templates
#         Build { ... },                 // build components
#         GenerateBridge { ... },        // generate WASM Bridge SDK
#         Repl { ... },                  // TypeScript REPL
#         Deploy { ... },                // deploy with plan/diff
#         Clean { ... },                 // clean build artifacts
#         UpdateAgents { ... },          // update agents to current ver
#         RedeployAgents { ... },        // redeploy with current ver
#         Exec { ... },                  // custom app commands
#         Account { ... },               // account management
#         AgentType { ... },             // agent type definitions
#         Api { ... },                   // API gateway management
#         ApiToken { ... },              // API token management
#         Component { ... },             // component management
#         Environment { ... },           // environment management
#         Plugin { ... },                // plugin management
#         Profile { ... },               // profile management
#         ResourceDefinition { ... },    // resource definitions
#         RetryPolicy { ... },           // retry policy management
#         Server { ... },                // standalone server mode
#         Agent { ... },                 // agent (worker) management
#     }
#
# Global flags (GolemCliGlobalFlags, flattened into every subcommand):
#     -F, --format <FORMAT>                    Output format (text/json/yaml)
#     -E, --environment <NAME>                  Select Golem environment
#     -L, --local                               Use "local" environment/profile
#     -C, --cloud                               Use "cloud" environment/profile
#     -A, --app-manifest-path <PATH>            Custom golem.yaml path
#     -X, --disable-app-manifest-discovery      Disable manifest discovery
#     -P, --preset <PRESET>                     Component presets
#         --profile <NAME>                      Select Golem profile
#         --config-dir <PATH>                   Custom config directory
#     -Y, --yes                                 Auto-confirm prompts
#         --show-sensitive                      Show sensitive values
#
# comfy-table is used in golem-cli's `*-list` outputs and the `deploy
# --plan` diff renderer to display dynamic-width terminal tables that
# fit in the current terminal regardless of column count.
#
# Five-axis distinctness from every other Rust Axis 10 library:
#
#   1. IMPERATIVE BUILDER WITHOUT DERIVE — comfy-table uses pure
#      runtime methods; tabled uses derive; cli-table (Rust) uses a
#      different derive.
#
#   2. CONTENT-ARRANGEMENT ENUM — comfy-table is the only Rust table
#      library exposing an explicit enum for column-sizing strategy
#      (Disabled/Static/Dynamic/DynamicFullWidth).
#
#   3. 12 PRESETS + COMPOSABLE MODIFIERS — comfy-table separates
#      base presets from in-place modifiers (UTF8_ROUND_CORNERS,
#      UTF8_SOLID_INNER_BORDERS).
#
#   4. FULL CROSSTERM COLOR + ATTRIBUTE INTEGRATION — comfy-table
#      uses crossterm's full Color enum (TRUECOLOR + 256-color +
#      16-color fallback) and Attribute enum.
#
#   5. ARNE BEER / PUEUE-ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE — comfy-table is by the
#      Arne Beer / Nukesor maintainer family (pueue task scheduler +
#      crossterm co-maintainership).
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# COMMAND-LINE OPTIONS (sourced directly from
# https://github.com/golemcloud/golem/blob/main/cli/golem-cli/src/command.rs
# GolemCliSubcommand enum + GolemCliGlobalFlags struct.)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1
typeset -A opt_args

local -a _golem_cmds _golem_format
_golem_cmds=(
    'new:create a new application, component, or agent'
    'templates:list or search application templates'
    'build:build all or selected components in the application'
    'generate-bridge:generate Bridge SDK(s) for selected agent(s)'
    'repl:start TypeScript REPL for a selected component'
    'deploy:deploy application'
    'clean:DESTRUCTIVE: remove build artifacts'
    'update-agents:auto-update existing agents to current version'
    'redeploy-agents:redeploy all agents using current version'
    'exec:execute custom app-defined commands (from golem.yaml)'
    'account:account management'
    'agent-type:agent type definitions'
    'api:API gateway management'
    'api-token:API token management'
    'component:component management'
    'environment:environment management'
    'plugin:plugin management'
    'profile:profile management'
    'resource-definition:resource definition management'
    'retry-policy:retry policy management'
    'server:standalone server mode'
    'agent:agent (worker) management'
    'help:show help for a subcommand'
    'completion:generate shell completion script'
)
_golem_format=(
    'text:human-readable text (default)'
    'json:JSON output'
    'yaml:YAML output'
)

_arguments -C \
    '(-F --format)'{-F+,--format=}'[output format]:format:(text json yaml)' \
    '(-E --environment)'{-E+,--environment=}'[select Golem environment]:environment:_default' \
    '(-L --local -C --cloud)'{-L,--local}'[use local environment/profile]' \
    '(-L --local -C --cloud)'{-C,--cloud}'[use cloud environment/profile]' \
    '(-A --app-manifest-path)'{-A+,--app-manifest-path=}'[custom golem.yaml path]:path:_files -g "*.{yaml,yml}"' \
    '(-X --disable-app-manifest-discovery)'{-X,--disable-app-manifest-discovery}'[disable manifest auto-discovery]' \
    '(-P --preset)'{-P+,--preset=}'[component presets (comma-separated)]:presets:_default' \
    '--profile=[select Golem profile]:profile:_default' \
    '--config-dir=[custom config dir (default \$HOME/.golem)]:dir:_directories' \
    '(-Y --yes)'{-Y,--yes}'[auto-confirm interactive prompts]' \
    '--show-sensitive[show sensitive values in text output]' \
    '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
    '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[show version]' \
    '1: :->cmd' \
    '*::arg:->args' \
    && ret=0

case $state in
    cmd)
        _describe -t commands 'golem-cli subcommand' _golem_cmds && ret=0
        ;;
    args)
        case $words[1] in
            new)
                _arguments \
                    '--application-name=[application name]:name:_default' \
                    '--component-name=[component name]:name:_default' \
                    '*--template=[template name]:template:_default' \
                    '1:application path:_directories' \
                    && ret=0
                ;;
            templates)
                _arguments \
                    '1:filter (language or name):_default' \
                    && ret=0
                ;;
            build)
                _arguments \
                    '*--component-name=[component name filter]:name:_default' \
                    && ret=0
                ;;
            generate-bridge)
                _arguments \
                    '--language=[target language]:language:(rust typescript javascript python go c)' \
                    '*--component-name=[component filter]:name:_default' \
                    '*--agent-type-name=[agent type filter]:name:_default' \
                    '--output-dir=[output directory]:dir:_directories' \
                    && ret=0
                ;;
            repl)
                _arguments \
                    '--language=[REPL language]:language:(typescript javascript)' \
                    '--component-name=[component name]:name:_default' \
                    '(-s --script)'{-s+,--script=}'[inline TypeScript script]:script:_default' \
                    '--script-file=[path to TypeScript script file]:file:_files -g "*.{ts,tsx,js,mjs}"' \
                    '--disable-stream[do not stream logs from invoked agents]' \
                    '--disable-auto-imports[disable Bridge SDK auto-imports]' \
                    && ret=0
                ;;
            deploy)
                _arguments \
                    '--plan[plan only, no changes (shows diff)]' \
                    '--full-diff[show full diff instead of changed entries only]' \
                    '--version=[rollback to version]:version:_default' \
                    '--revision=[rollback to revision id]:revision:_default' \
                    && ret=0
                ;;
            clean|update-agents|redeploy-agents)
                _arguments \
                    '*--component-name=[component filter]:name:_default' \
                    && ret=0
                ;;
            help)
                _describe -t commands 'subcommand' _golem_cmds && ret=0
                ;;
            completion)
                _values 'shell' bash zsh fish powershell elvish && ret=0
                ;;
        esac
        ;;
esac

return ret
